1. VISION & MISSION
- Create the most engaging, effective, and faith-building prayer app ever made.
- Combine proven habit-formation science (implementation intentions, gratitude psychology, active engagement) with deep Duolingo/Habitica-style gamification.
- Goal: Help users “pray without ceasing” (1 Thessalonians 5:17), cultivate an intimate walk with God, and build lifelong prayer habits that actually stick — while visibly seeing the fruit of their prayers through answered testimonies, a growing record of God’s blessings, and shared prayer support in community.
- Differentiator: Rich multi-sensory prayer modes, powerful reward system for actually praying, seamless voice-to-text, answer-tracking with partial updates, a beautiful catalogue of famous prayers, a dedicated daily Gratitude section with photo attachments, and strictly invite-only Prayer Groups for shared intercession — far beyond Pray.com, Echo Prayer, Abide, or Prayer Notebook.

2. TARGET AUDIENCE
- Christians of all ages who want consistent prayer but struggle with distraction or dry spells.
- Teens, young adults, busy parents, pastors, small groups, and families.
- Auditory, kinesthetic, reflective, and competitive learners.

3.1 Prayer Engagement Engine - "Many Options & Tricks"
The core of PrayerQuest is a rich, multi-sensory prayer engine that gives users 10+ different ways to actually pray any topic, list, or famous prayer. Every mode is designed purely for engagement and expression — there is no memorization or spaced-repetition scheduler for prayer items.

Goal: Prevent prayer boredom, support every learning style, and maximize long-term habit formation through joyful, rewarding prayer action.

