3.5 Gratitude Section — Daily Gratitude Practice [NEEDS IMPLEMENTING]
Purpose: Build a powerful daily habit of thanksgiving (1 Thessalonians 5:18) that strengthens faith, improves mood, and visibly records God’s blessings in users’ lives. This section is fully integrated with the gamification system and works alongside prayer sessions.

- **Daily Gratitude Prompt**
  - Every day (triggered by notification or Home screen card) the user is gently prompted: “What are you thankful for today?”
  - User chooses to log **1, 3, or 5 gratitudes** per day (selectable via chips or settings preset).
  - Simple, encouraging interface with voice-to-text support for each entry.
  - Optional prompt suggestions (e.g., “Something God did today”, “A person I’m thankful for”, “A small blessing”, faith-themed prompts pulled from Scripture).

- **Gratitude Entry Features**
  - Each gratitude can include:
    - Short text description (voice-to-text button prominently featured)
    - Optional photo attachment (camera or gallery picker, stored locally with compression)
    - Category tag (e.g., Family, Provision, Nature, Spiritual Growth, Health)
    - Link to a related prayer item (optional)
  - Entries are timestamped and saved to the user’s personal Gratitude Catalogue.

- **Gratitude Catalogue**
  - Dedicated screen showing a beautiful, chronological or grid view of all past gratitudes.
  - Filter by date, category, or photo-only.
  - Timeline or calendar heat-map view to see consistency.
  - Search by keyword.
  - Option to revisit, edit, or add a photo later.
  - Export or share individual entries as image cards (with verse overlay option).

- **Gamification Integration**
  - Completing the daily gratitude prompt counts toward daily quests and streak protection.
  - Bonus XP based on number chosen (1 = base, 3 = medium, 5 = high) and whether a photo was attached.
  - New badges added:
    - Gratitude Starter (first 7 days)
    - Thankful Heart (30 consecutive days)
    - Abundance Mindset (100 total gratitudes)
    - Photo Gratitude (50 entries with photos)
    - Faithful Thanksgiver (milestones for total volume)
  - Streaks and hearts can be protected or extended by consistent gratitude logging.

- **Technical Notes**
  - New Room entity: GratitudeEntry (id, date, text, photoUri, category, linkedPrayerId, timestamp)
  - Reuses existing image handling and voice-to-text plumbing.
  - Fully offline; photos stored in app-private storage.

3.6 Prayer Groups — Shared Community Prayer [NEEDS IMPLEMENTING]
Purpose: Enable users to create or join strictly invite-only Prayer Groups so they can pray together with friends, family, small groups, or church communities. This adds powerful social accountability and encouragement while keeping the focus on actual prayer.

- **Core Features**
  - Users can create a new Prayer Group with a name, description, emoji/icon.
  - Each group generates a unique **shareable invite code** (e.g., “PRAY-8K9M2X”). Only people who receive and enter this code can join.
  - No public browsing or discovery of groups — completely invite-only.
  - Group members can view the shared active prayer list.
  - When any member adds a new prayer request to the group, all members receive a gentle in-app notification (“Sarah added a new request: ‘Healing for Mom’”).
  - Members can mark that they have prayed for a group item (with one tap or via any prayer mode). The item shows a count of how many people have prayed for it (e.g., “Prayed by 4 members”).
  - Optional activity feed showing recent prayer activity in the group (who prayed and when — without revealing private journal content).
  - Each group item supports the same update flow as personal prayers: partial answer, modification, or move to Answered.

- **Privacy & Safety**
  - Groups are strictly private and invite-only via share code.
  - Members can leave a group at any time.
  - Group admins (the creator + optional additional roles) can remove members or moderate requests.

- **Gamification Integration**
  - Praying for group items earns bonus XP and contributes to daily quests.
  - New badges for group participation:
    - Group Prayer Warrior (first group joined)
    - Faithful Intercessor (pray for 50 group requests)
    - Community Builder (create 5 groups)
    - United in Prayer (milestones for total group prayers logged)

- **Technical Notes**
  - New Room entities: PrayerGroup (id, name, description, emoji, shareCode, createdBy)
  - GroupPrayerItemCrossRef for many-to-many linking between groups and prayer items.
  - PrayerGroupMember entity to track membership and roles.
  - MVP version is fully offline with manual refresh. Real-time notifications and sync are [POST-MVP] (requires cloud backend).

